== Intent == 

an [[Object-XML mapping]] technology for [[Language:Java]]

== Description ==

JAXB consists of the schema compiler [[Technology:xjc]] and a library that supports un-/marshaling. 
JAXB is typically used for [[schema-first mapping]] so that one generates Java classes and interfaces
from an XML schema (i.e., an element of the [[Language:XSD]] language. Arguably, JAXB can also be said to provide the capability of [[Open serialization|(open) serialization]] based on [[Language:XML]] as serialization format.

